Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(63):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(63):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(63):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(63):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(63):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(63):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(63):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x

Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(63):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(63):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(63):     // check for IE3\n
Action.c(63):     var isIE3 = (navigator.appVersion.indexOf('MSIE 3') != -1);\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n

Action.c(63):               alertText += beginRequestAlertForText + realName + endRequestAlert + hardReturn;

Action.c(63):               alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(63):             }\n

Action.c(63):             if (allAtOnce) {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText += str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText = str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             }\n

Action.c(63):               alertText += beginFormatAlert + elts[i].format + hardReturn;\n

Action.c(63):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n

Action.c(63):             }\n

Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(63):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(63):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(63):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(63):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(63):     // check for IE3\n
Action.c(63):     var isIE3 = (navigator.appVersion.indexOf('MSIE 3') != -1);\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n

Action.c(63):     **   isSelect(formObj): verifies item from a select menu is chosen\n
Action.c(63):     **   isRadio(formObj): verifies one of a group of radio buttons is chosen\n
Action.c(63):     **   isCheck(formObj, form, [begin], [num]): verifies at least one\n
Action.c(63):     **       of a group of checkboxes is checked\n

Action.c(63):     **         of the first checkbox (remember to start counting from zero)\n

Action.c(63):       }\n
Action.c(63):       return false;\n

Action.c(63):      month == 12) {\n
Action.c(63):         if (day > 31) { return false }\n

Action.c(63):         realName = elts[i].realName;\n

Action.c(63):           str = formObj.value;\n
Action.c(63):     \n

Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):           if (str == "") {\n
Action.c(63):             if (allAtOnce) {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText += beginRequestAlertForText + realName + endRequestAlert + hardReturn;
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText = beginRequestAlertForText + realName + endRequestAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):               alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(63):             }\n
Action.c(63):           } else {\n
Action.c(63):             if (allAtOnce) {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText += str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText = str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             }\n
Action.c(63):             if (elts[i].format != null) {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText += beginFormatAlert + elts[i].format + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             }\n
Action.c(63):             if (allAtOnce) {\n
Action.c(63):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n
Action.c(63):               alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(63):             }\n
Action.c(63):           }\n
Action.c(63):         } else {\n
Action.c(63):           if (eval(elts[i].upToSnuff)) continue;\n

Action.c(63):     // check for IE3\n
Action.c(63):     var isIE3 = (navigator.appVersion.indexOf('MSIE 3') != -1);\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n

Action.c(63):      month == 12) {\n

Action.c(63):               alertText += beginRequestAlertForText + realName + endRequestAlert + hardReturn;
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n

Action.c(63):             }\n

Action.c(63):             if (allAtOnce) {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText += str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n
Action.c(63):               alertText = str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             }\n

Action.c(63):               alertText += beginFormatAlert + elts[i].format + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(63):             }\n

Action.c(63):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(63):             } else {\n

Action.c(63):             }\n

Action.c(63):     // check for IE3\n
Action.c(63):     var isIE3 = (navigator.appVersion.indexOf('MSIE 3') != -1);\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(63):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(63):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(63):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(63):     **     text\n
Action.c(63):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(63):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(63):     **     radio\n
Action.c(63):     **     select\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(63):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(63):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(63):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(63):     **\n
Action.c(63):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(63):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(63):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     // object definition\n
Action.c(63):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(63):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(63):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(63):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(63):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(63):     }\n
Action.c(63):     \n
Action.c(63):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(63):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(63):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(63):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
